## RELEVANT CLINICAL GUIDELINES (Evidence-Based)
[G044] Urinary Tract Infection (IDSA UTI Guidelines 2011): Uncomplicated UTI: nitrofurantoin or trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole 3-7 days. Fosfomycin single dose. Avoid fluoroquinolones for uncomplicated UTI. Urine culture if recurrent.
[G025] Acute Kidney Injury (KDIGO AKI Guidelines 2012): AKI defined as creatinine rise ≥0.3 mg/dL in 48h or ≥1.5× baseline in 7 days or urine output <0.5 mL/kg/h for 6h. Avoid nephrotoxins. Adequate hydration essential.
[G024] Chronic Kidney Disease (KDIGO CKD Guidelines 2022): ACE inhibitor or ARB recommended in CKD with proteinuria. Monitor potassium levels. Anemia management with ESA when Hb <10 g/dL. SGLT-2 inhibitors reduce CKD progression.
[G041] Iron Deficiency (British Society of Haematology Guidelines): Ferritin <30 mcg/L diagnostic of iron deficiency. Ferritin 30-100 with transferrin saturation <20% suggests functional deficiency. Investigate GI blood loss in adults.
[G042] Vitamin B12 Deficiency (British National Formulary): Causes: pernicious anemia, veganism, malabsorption. Symptoms: fatigue, glossitis, peripheral neuropathy, subacute combined degeneration of cord. Check anti-IF antibodies.

