[G028] Migraine (AHS Migraine Treatment Guidelines 2021): Acute: triptans first-line for moderate-severe migraine. NSAIDs for mild. Preventive therapy if ≥4 headache days/month. Topiramate, propranolol, or CGRP antagonists.
[G016] Dengue (WHO Dengue Guidelines 2012): Warning signs: abdominal pain, persistent vomiting, bleeding, lethargy, liver enlargement >2cm, rising hematocrit with rapid platelet fall. Require hospital admission.
